<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Shaun's Fitness Plan</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --green-dark: #085041;
    --green-mid: #1D9E75;
    --green-light: #E1F5EE;
    --green-text: #085041;
    --purple-dark: #3C3489;
    --purple-mid: #534AB7;
    --purple-light: #EEEDFE;
    --purple-text: #3C3489;
    --coral-dark: #712B13;
    --coral-light: #FAECE7;
    --amber-dark: #633806;
    --amber-light: #FAEEDA;
    --blue-dark: #0C447C;
    --blue-light: #E6F1FB;
    --gray-bg: #F7F6F2;
    --gray-border: #E2E0D8;
    --text-primary: #1a1a18;
    --text-secondary: #5F5E5A;
    --white: #ffffff;
    --radius-sm: 6px;
    --radius-md: 10px;
    --radius-lg: 14px;
  }

  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  body {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    background: var(--gray-bg);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  /* NAV */
  .top-nav {
    background: var(--white);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-border);
    padding: 0 2rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 100;
  }

  .nav-brand {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--green-dark);
    padding: 1rem 0;
    margin-right: 2rem;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .nav-tabs {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .nav-tab {
    padding: 1.1rem 1.4rem;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
    background: none;
    border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
    transition: all 0.15s;
    white-space: nowrap;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  }

  .nav-tab:hover { color: var(--text-primary); }
  .nav-tab.active { color: var(--green-dark); border-bottom-color: var(--green-mid); font-weight: 500; }

  /* PAGES */
  .page { display: none; max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
  .page.active { display: block; }

  /* PAGE HEADER */
  .page-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .page-header h1 { font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 32px; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .page-header p { font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-secondary); font-weight: 300; }

  /* STAT ROW */
  .stat-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .stat-card { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--gray-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 14px 16px; }
  .stat-label { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-secondary); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .stat-value { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); }

  /* DAY TABS */
  .day-tabs { display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .day-tab {
    padding: 7px 15px; font-size: 13px; border: 1px solid var(--gray-border);
    border-radius: 20px; cursor: pointer; background: var(--white);
    color: var(--text-secondary); transition: all 0.15s; font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  }
  .day-tab:hover { border-color: var(--green-mid); color: var(--green-dark); }
  .day-tab.active { background: var(--green-dark); border-color: var(--green-dark); color: #9FE1CB; font-weight: 500; }

  /* WORKOUT CARD */
  .workout-card { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--gray-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); overflow: hidden; }
  .workout-header { padding: 16px 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-border); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
  .workout-title { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; flex: 1; }
  .duration-chip { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); background: var(--gray-bg); padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 20px; }

  .section-block { padding: 16px 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-border); }
  .section-block:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .section-title { font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.07em; color: var(--text-secondary); font-weight: 500; margin-bottom: 12px; }

  .ex-row { display: flex; align-items: center; padding: 8px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #F0EEE8; gap: 12px; }
  .ex-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .ex-name { font-size: 14px; flex: 1; }
  .ex-sets { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); white-space: nowrap; }

  .tip-block { margin: 16px 20px; padding: 12px 14px; background: var(--green-light); border-left: 3px solid var(--green-mid); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); font-size: 13px; color: var(--green-text); line-height: 1.6; }
  .tip-block strong { font-weight: 500; }

  /* BADGE */
  .badge { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 500; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 20px; white-space: nowrap; }
  .badge-upper { background: var(--blue-light); color: var(--blue-dark); }
  .badge-hiit { background: var(--coral-light); color: var(--coral-dark); }
  .badge-lower { background: var(--green-light); color: var(--green-text); }
  .badge-pull { background: var(--purple-light); color: var(--purple-text); }
  .badge-full { background: var(--amber-light); color: var(--amber-dark); }
  .badge-rest { background: var(--gray-bg); color: var(--text-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--gray-border); }

  /* MEAL PLAN */
  .plan-tabs { display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .plan-tab {
    padding: 7px 15px; font-size: 13px; border: 1px solid var(--gray-border);
    border-radius: 20px; cursor: pointer; background: var(--white);
    color: var(--text-secondary); transition: all 0.15s; font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  }
  .plan-tab:hover { border-color: var(--green-mid); color: var(--green-dark); }
  .plan-tab.active { background: var(--green-dark); border-color: var(--green-dark); color: #9FE1CB; font-weight: 500; }

  .meal-card { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--gray-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .meal-header { padding: 13px 18px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-border); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; }
  .meal-title { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 500; flex: 1; }
  .cal-chip { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); background: var(--gray-bg); padding: 3px 9px; border-radius: 20px; }

  .badge-coffee { background: var(--amber-light); color: var(--amber-dark); }
  .badge-lunch { background: var(--green-light); color: var(--green-text); }
  .badge-snack { background: var(--purple-light); color: var(--purple-text); }
  .badge-dinner { background: var(--coral-light); color: var(--coral-dark); }
  .badge-protein { background: var(--blue-light); color: var(--blue-dark); }

  .food-row { display: flex; align-items: center; padding: 9px 18px; border-bottom: 1px solid #F0EEE8; gap: 12px; }
  .food-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .food-name { font-size: 14px; flex: 1; }
  .food-portion { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .food-cal { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); min-width: 60px; text-align: right; }

  .macro-row { padding: 10px 18px; display: flex; gap: 18px; border-top: 1px solid #F0EEE8; background: #FAFAF8; }
  .macro-item { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .macro-item span { font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); }

  .total-bar { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--gray-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 14px 18px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; margin-top: 4px; }
  .total-label { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .total-value { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); }

  .green-tip { background: var(--green-light); border-left: 3px solid var(--green-mid); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); padding: 12px 14px; margin-top: 12px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--green-text); line-height: 1.6; }
  .green-tip strong { font-weight: 500; }

  /* NUTRITION PAGE */
  .info-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .info-card { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--gray-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 16px 18px; }
  .info-card h3 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .info-card p { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }
  .info-card p strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }

  .avoid-list, .good-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .avoid-list li, .good-list li { font-size: 13px; padding: 7px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #F0EEE8; color: var(--text-secondary); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; }
  .avoid-list li:last-child, .good-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .dot-red { width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: #E24B4A; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .dot-green { width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--green-mid); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .section-heading { font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--text-primary); }

  .hidden { display: none; }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .stat-row { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
    .info-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .top-nav { padding: 0 1rem; }
    .page { padding: 1.5rem 1rem; }
    .nav-brand { font-size: 16px; margin-right: 1rem; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<nav class="top-nav">
  <div class="nav-brand">Shaun's Plan</div>
  <div class="nav-tabs">
    <button class="nav-tab active" data-page="workout">Workout</button>
    <button class="nav-tab" data-page="meals">Meal Plan</button>
    <button class="nav-tab" data-page="nutrition">Nutrition Guide</button>
  </div>
</nav>

<!-- ===== WORKOUT PAGE ===== -->
<div class="page active" id="page-workout">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>5-Day calisthenics program</h1>
    <p>Age 47 &nbsp;·&nbsp; 5'10" &nbsp;·&nbsp; 215 lbs &nbsp;·&nbsp; Goal: lose 30 lbs</p>
  </div>

  <div class="stat-row">
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-label">Training days</div><div class="stat-value">5 / week</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-label">Session length</div><div class="stat-value">40–55 min</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-label">Rest days</div><div class="stat-value">Sat + Sun</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-label">Goal</div><div class="stat-value">–30 lbs</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="day-tabs">
    <button class="day-tab active" data-day="mon">Monday</button>
    <button class="day-tab" data-day="tue">Tuesday</button>
    <button class="day-tab" data-day="wed">Wednesday</button>
    <button class="day-tab" data-day="thu">Thursday</button>
    <button class="day-tab" data-day="fri">Friday</button>
    <button class="day-tab" data-day="wknd">Weekend</button>
  </div>

  <!-- MONDAY -->
  <div class="workout-card" id="day-mon">
    <div class="workout-header">
      <span class="badge badge-upper">Upper body + core</span>
      <span class="workout-title">Push &amp; stabilize</span>
      <span class="duration-chip">45–50 min</span>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">Warm-up — 5 min</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Arm circles + shoulder rolls</span><span class="ex-sets">60 sec</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Hip circles</span><span class="ex-sets">60 sec</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Inchworms</span><span class="ex-sets">6 reps</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Jumping jacks</span><span class="ex-sets">30 sec</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">Main circuit — 3 rounds, 60 sec rest between rounds</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Push-ups (regular or incline)</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 10–15</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Pike push-ups</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 8–10</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Tricep dips (chair)</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 10–12</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Plank hold</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 30–45 sec</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Dead bug</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 8 each side</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Side plank</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 20 sec each</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-block"><strong>Belly focus tip:</strong> On every plank and push-up, actively brace your core like you're about to take a punch. This turns basic moves into deep core work.</div>
  </div>

  <!-- TUESDAY -->
  <div class="workout-card hidden" id="day-tue">
    <div class="workout-header">
      <span class="badge badge-hiit">HIIT cardio</span>
      <span class="workout-title">Metabolic burn</span>
      <span class="duration-chip">40–45 min</span>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">Warm-up — 5 min</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">March in place</span><span class="ex-sets">90 sec</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Leg swings (front/back + lateral)</span><span class="ex-sets">10 each</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">High knees (light pace)</span><span class="ex-sets">30 sec</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">HIIT block — 4 rounds of 20 sec on / 40 sec off</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Jump squats (or squat to calf raise)</span><span class="ex-sets">20 sec on</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Mountain climbers</span><span class="ex-sets">20 sec on</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Burpees (step-out version is fine)</span><span class="ex-sets">20 sec on</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">High knees</span><span class="ex-sets">20 sec on</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">Finisher — steady state</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Brisk walk or easy jog in place</span><span class="ex-sets">10 min</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-block"><strong>Love handle tip:</strong> HIIT is the best tool for stubborn fat around the obliques. High-intensity intervals drive the hormonal response that burns visceral fat first in most people.</div>
  </div>

  <!-- WEDNESDAY -->
  <div class="workout-card hidden" id="day-wed">
    <div class="workout-header">
      <span class="badge badge-lower">Lower body + core</span>
      <span class="workout-title">Legs &amp; stability</span>
      <span class="duration-chip">45–50 min</span>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">Warm-up — 5 min</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Bodyweight squats (slow)</span><span class="ex-sets">10 reps</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Hip flexor stretch (kneeling)</span><span class="ex-sets">30 sec each</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Glute bridges</span><span class="ex-sets">10 reps</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">Main circuit — 3 rounds</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Bodyweight squats</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 15–20</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Reverse lunges</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 10 each leg</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Glute bridge hold</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 30 sec</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Step-ups (chair or stair)</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 10 each</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Hollow body hold</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 20 sec</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Bicycle crunches</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 15 each side</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-block"><strong>Why legs matter for the belly:</strong> Your legs are your biggest muscle group. Training them hard burns more calories and raises your resting metabolic rate — the single best lever for long-term fat loss at 47+.</div>
  </div>

  <!-- THURSDAY -->
  <div class="workout-card hidden" id="day-thu">
    <div class="workout-header">
      <span class="badge badge-pull">Core focus + pull</span>
      <span class="workout-title">Pull &amp; compress</span>
      <span class="duration-chip">45 min</span>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">Warm-up — 5 min</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Cat-cow stretch</span><span class="ex-sets">10 reps</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Thoracic rotation</span><span class="ex-sets">8 each side</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Band pull-aparts (or towel)</span><span class="ex-sets">15 reps</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">Main circuit — 3 rounds</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Inverted rows (table or low bar)</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 8–12</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Superman holds</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 10 (3 sec hold)</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Plank to downward dog</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 8</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Leg raises (lying flat)</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 12</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Russian twists</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 15 each side</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Flutter kicks</span><span class="ex-sets">3 × 20 sec</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-block"><strong>Oblique note:</strong> Russian twists and side planks directly work the obliques — the muscles under love handles. Build them and the area firms up as fat drops.</div>
  </div>

  <!-- FRIDAY -->
  <div class="workout-card hidden" id="day-fri">
    <div class="workout-header">
      <span class="badge badge-full">Full body HIIT</span>
      <span class="workout-title">End-of-week burn</span>
      <span class="duration-chip">45–50 min</span>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">Warm-up — 5 min</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Full body dynamic stretch</span><span class="ex-sets">5 min</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">Full-body circuit — 4 rounds, 45 sec rest between rounds</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Push-ups</span><span class="ex-sets">max reps</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Squat jumps (or prisoner squats)</span><span class="ex-sets">12–15</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Mountain climbers</span><span class="ex-sets">20 sec</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Reverse lunges alternating</span><span class="ex-sets">10 each leg</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Plank shoulder taps</span><span class="ex-sets">10 each side</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Burpees</span><span class="ex-sets">8–10</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">Cool-down — 5–7 min</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Child's pose</span><span class="ex-sets">60 sec</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Figure-4 glute stretch</span><span class="ex-sets">30 sec each</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Chest opener stretch</span><span class="ex-sets">30 sec</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-block"><strong>Progress marker:</strong> Each week, try to add 1–2 reps or 5 sec to each movement. Progressive overload is what drives continued fat loss after the first few weeks.</div>
  </div>

  <!-- WEEKEND -->
  <div class="workout-card hidden" id="day-wknd">
    <div class="workout-header">
      <span class="badge badge-rest">Active recovery</span>
      <span class="workout-title">Saturday + Sunday</span>
      <span class="duration-chip">Optional movement</span>
    </div>
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-title">What to do on your off days</div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">30–45 min walk (flat or hills)</span><span class="ex-sets">Ideal</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Light stretching or yoga</span><span class="ex-sets">20–30 min</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Swimming or cycling (easy pace)</span><span class="ex-sets">Optional</span></div>
      <div class="ex-row"><span class="ex-name">Full rest — no workout</span><span class="ex-sets">At least 1 day</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-block"><strong>Recovery matters more at 47+:</strong> Testosterone and growth hormone recovery takes longer with age. Taking real rest days preserves muscle, keeps cortisol in check, and prevents the plateau that kills most programs.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ===== MEAL PLAN PAGE ===== -->
<div class="page" id="page-meals">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>1,500 calorie meal plan</h1>
    <p>No breakfast · Coffee only in the morning · No fish · Easy-to-cook proteins</p>
  </div>

  <div class="stat-row">
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-label">Daily calories</div><div class="stat-value">~1,500</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-label">Protein target</div><div class="stat-value">~150g</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-label">Meals per day</div><div class="stat-value">3 + coffee</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-label">No fish</div><div class="stat-value">Ever</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="plan-tabs">
